name: Pasture Canyon
description:
Introduction

The canyon starts out with a dozen nice downclimbs. The 3 rappels come one after another descending into a deep, beautifully sculpted cavern. The 3rd rappel is a fairly easy DC. Two short pools can be stemmed over to avoid getting wet. The exit is very long and by the end of it you may forget how great the canyon was. If ascending up West Fork there are a couple R-rated chimneys to ascend that are blocked at the top by large chockstones forcing you to go out on smooth walls.
